SENATE BILL No. 110
_____
DIGEST OF INTRODUCED BILL
Citations Affected: IC 21-20-3.
Synopsis: Indiana University board of trustees. Amends the
membership of the board of trustees of Indiana University.
Effective: Upon passage.
Glick, Walker G
December 9, 2025, read first time and referred to Committee on Education and Career
Development.
2026 IN 110—LS 6405/DI 110

Introduced
Second Regular Session of the 124th General Assembly (2026)
PRINTING CODE. Amendments: Whenever an existing statute (or a section of the Indiana
Constitution) is being amended, the text of the existing provision will appear in this style type,
additions will appear in this style type, and deletions will appear in this style type.
Additions: Whenever a new statutory provision is being enacted (or a new constitutional
provision adopted), the text of the new provision will appear in this style type. Also, the
word NEW will appear in that style type in the introductory clause of each SECTION that adds
a new provision to the Indiana Code or the Indiana Constitution.
Conflict reconciliation: Text in a statute in this style type or this style type reconciles conflicts
between statutes enacted by the 2025 Regular Session of the General Assembly.
SENATE BILL No. 110
A BILL FOR AN ACT to amend the Indiana Code concerning
higher education.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
1 SECTION 1. IC 21-20-3-2, AS AMENDED BY P.L.213-2025,
2 SECTION 253, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS
3 [EFFECTIVE UPON PASSAGE]: Sec. 2. (a) The board of trustees has
4 nine (9) members. appointed by the governor.
5 (b) At least five (5) of the members appointed to the board of
6 trustees must be alumni of Indiana University.
7 SECTION 2. IC 21-20-3-2.5 IS REPEALED [EFFECTIVE UPON
8 PASSAGE]. Sec. 2.5. (a) The governor may at any time remove and
9 replace a member of the board of trustees who was elected by the
10 alumni of Indiana University.
11 (b) If the governor removes and replaces a member under this
12 section, the new member appointed by the governor serves until the
13 expiration of the term of the replaced member described in subsection
14 (a).
15 (c) If the governor does not remove and replace a member under this
16 section, the member of the board of trustees elected by the alumni of
17 Indiana University may serve until the member's term expires.
2026 IN 110—LS 6405/DI 110

2
1 (d) This section expires January 1, 2028.
2 SECTION 3. IC 21-20-3-3, AS AMENDED BY P.L.213-2025,
3 SECTION 255, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS
4 [EFFECTIVE UPON PASSAGE]: Sec. 3. (a) At least five (5) of the
5 members appointed to the board of trustees must be residents of
6 Indiana.
7 (b) This subsection section does not apply to the student trustee
8 appointed to the board of trustees. Not more than: three (3) of the
9 members of the board of trustees
10 (1) one (1) of the trustees elected to the board of trustees; and
11 (2) two (2) of the trustees appointed to the board of trustees;
12 may reside in the same county.
13 SECTION 4. IC 21-20-3-3.5 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA CODE
14 AS A NEW SECTION TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
15 UPON PASSAGE]: Sec. 3.5. (a) Three (3) members of the board of
16 trustees shall be elected by the alumni of Indiana University under
17 this chapter. In the year in which the term of any member of the
18 board of trustees elected by the alumni expires, a successor to the
19 trustee shall be elected by the alumni of Indiana University, to
20 serve for a term of three (3) years beginning July 1 next succeeding
21 the election.
22 (b) When a vacancy occurs in the membership of the board of
23 trustees who are elected by the alumni, because of death,
24 resignation, or any other reason, the vacancy shall be filled by
25 selection by the Indiana University alumni association executive
26 council for the unexpired term.
27 SECTION 5. IC 21-20-3-4.5 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA CODE
28 AS A NEW SECTION TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
29 UPON PASSAGE]: Sec. 4.5. The members of the board of trustees
30 who are elected by the alumni of Indiana University must be
31 alumni of Indiana University.
32 SECTION 6. IC 21-20-3-5.5 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA CODE
33 AS A NEW SECTION TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
34 UPON PASSAGE]: Sec. 5.5. The alumni of Indiana University
35 consist of those persons who have been awarded a degree by the
36 board of trustees of Indiana University as recommended by the
37 faculty.
38 SECTION 7. IC 21-20-3-6.5 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA CODE
39 AS A NEW SECTION TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
40 UPON PASSAGE]: Sec. 6.5. (a) Any one hundred (100) or more
41 alumni of Indiana University may file with the librarian of Indiana
42 University on or before April 1 in each year a written nomination
2026 IN 110—LS 6405/DI 110

3
1 for a trustee to be elected by the alumni at the next election.
2 (b) After April 1, but not later than June 1, a list of all
3 candidates nominated under this section shall be mailed by the
4 librarian to each alumnus at the alumnus's address.
5 SECTION 8. IC 21-20-3-7.5 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA CODE
6 AS A NEW SECTION TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
7 UPON PASSAGE]: Sec. 7.5. Beginning in the 2026 calendar year,
8 the election of members of the board of trustees shall be held at
9 Indiana University on the secular day immediately preceding July
10 1. At that time trustees shall be elected to:
11 (1) serve for a term of three (3) years from July 1 next
12 succeeding the trustee's election; and
13 (2) complete any unexpired term or terms.
14 SECTION 9. IC 21-20-3-8.5 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA CODE
15 AS A NEW SECTION TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
16 UPON PASSAGE]: Sec. 8.5. The university librarian shall conduct
17 the elections to select the three (3) alumni members of the board of
18 trustees. All alumni (as described in section 5.5 of this chapter) are
19 eligible to participate in the election either by electronic or printed
20 ballot, and each eligible individual may cast only one (1) vote. A
21 request for a printed ballot must be made in writing to the
22 university librarian not later than May 1 of an election year. The
23 university librarian may adopt rules and regulations as necessary
24 to carry out this section.
25 SECTION 10. IC 21-20-3-9.5 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA
26 CODE AS A NEW SECTION TO READ AS FOLLOWS
27 [EFFECTIVE UPON PASSAGE]: Sec. 9.5. The person receiving the
28 greatest number of votes cast shall be declared the elected trustee.
29 If two (2) or more persons receive an equal and the greatest
30 number of votes cast, the librarian shall cast lots to determine
31 which of the persons shall be declared the elected trustee.
32 SECTION 11. IC 21-20-3-10.5 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA
33 CODE AS A NEW SECTION TO READ AS FOLLOWS
34 [EFFECTIVE UPON PASSAGE]: Sec. 10.5. The term of an elected
35 trustee expires July 1 of the year in which the terms are to end.
36 SECTION 12. IC 21-20-3-11.5 IS REPEALED [EFFECTIVE
37 UPON PASSAGE]. Sec. 11.5. Except for the student trustee described
38 in section 13 of this chapter, an employee of Indiana University may
39 not serve as a member of the board of trustees.
40 SECTION 13. IC 21-20-3-12, AS AMENDED BY P.L.213-2025,
41 SECTION 265, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS
42 [EFFECTIVE UPON PASSAGE]: Sec. 12. (a) Except for a student
