1 trustee described in section 13 of this chapter, each member The
2 governor shall appoint five (5) members of the board of trustees
3 serves for a term terms of three (3) years.
4 (b) A member of the board of trustees may not serve more than three
5 (3) terms.
6 (c) (b) Whenever a vacancy occurs in the membership of the board
7 of trustees who are appointed by the governor because of death or
8 resignation or for any other reason, the vacancy shall be filled by an
9 appointment of the governor for the unexpired term.
10 SECTION 14. IC 21-20-3-13, AS AMENDED BY P.L.213-2025,
11 SECTION 266, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS
12 [EFFECTIVE UPON PASSAGE]: Sec. 13. (a) One (1) member
13 appointed The governor shall appoint to the board of trustees a
14 member who must be a full-time student of Indiana University during
15 the two (2) year tenure of the appointment.
16 (b) The student trustee appointed in accordance with this section
17 serves for a term of one (1) year.
18 SECTION 15. IC 21-20-3-17 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA
19 CODE AS A NEW SECTION TO READ AS FOLLOWS
20 [EFFECTIVE UPON PASSAGE]: Sec. 17. (a) This section does not
21 apply to the:
22 (1) student trustee appointed to the board of trustees under
23 this chapter; or
24 (2) other members of the board of trustees whose terms expire
25 in June 2026.
26 (b) Notwithstanding any other provision in this chapter, an
27 election by the alumni of Indiana University shall be held as
28 described in this chapter to elect three (3) members of the board of
29 trustees. The following apply to the three (3) members elected as
30 provided in this section in 2026:
31 (1) The three (3) elected members replace the members of the
32 board of trustees who were appointed as new members by the
33 governor in June 2025.
34 (2) Each alumnus described in section 5.5 of this chapter may
35 cast three (3) votes in the 2026 election. However, an alumnus
36 may not cast more than one (1) vote for the same candidate.
37 (3) The initial term of each elected member is as follows:
38 (A) The individual who receives the greatest number of
39 votes cast shall be declared an elected trustee and serve an
40 initial term of three (3) years.
41 (B) The individual who receives the second greatest
42 number of votes cast shall be declared an elected trustee
2026 IN 110—LS 6405/DI 110

5
1 and serve an initial term of two (2) years.
2 (C) The individual who receives the third greatest number
3 of votes cast shall be declared an elected trustee and serve
4 an initial term of one (1) year.
5 (4) If two (2) or more persons described in subdivision (3)
6 receive an equal number of votes cast for one (1) elected
7 trustee position, the librarian shall cast lots to determine
8 which of the persons shall be declared the elected trustee.
9 (5) The term of each elected member begins July 1, 2026.
10 (6) The term of a each elected member expires July 1 of the
11 year in which the terms are to end.
12 (c) This section expires July 1, 2030.
13 SECTION 16. An emergency is declared for this act.
